Package: MicSim
Type: Package
Title: Performing Continuous-Time Microsimulation 
Version: 3.0.0
Date: 2022-11-01
Authors@R: c(person("Sabine", "Zinn", email = "szinn@diw.de", role = "aut"),
   	person("Felix", "von Heusinger", email = "fvonheusinger@diw.de", role = "cre"),
	person("Camila", "Weber", email = "cweber@diw.de", role = "ctb"),
	person("Claudio","Bosco", role = "ctb", email = "Claudio.BOSCO@ec.europa.eu"),
    	person("Maurizio","Teobaldell", role = "ctb", email = "Maurizio.TEOBALDELLI@ext.ec.europa.eu"))
Description: This toolkit allows performing continuous-time microsimulation for a wide range of life science (demography, social sciences, epidemiology) applications. Individual life-courses are specified by a continuous-time multi-state model as described in Zinn (2014) <doi:10.34196/IJM.00105>. 
